#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""sable-reconcile-handoffs — the pull-based reconciliation floor (SABLE-jfg6.3 / D3).

The push-based `post-push-merge-notify` hook fires ON the push, so any push whose
hook is unwired, races the remote's ref-update, or dies mid-flight leaves a merge
STRANDED: the branch is on origin, the work is done, but no `for-chuck` handoff
ever reached Chuck (research F4 — push-based notify provably misses). This tool is
the backstop for exactly that class: it does NOT sit on the push path, it QUERIES
the systems of record (origin + beads) and reconciles what it finds
(Anthropic's own "query systems of record and reconcile" pattern; TRADEOFFS #2).
It promotes chuck.md's prose stranded-recovery sweep (chuck.md §Boundaries) to code.

HELD IS A THIRD OUTCOME, NOT A SUPPRESSION (SABLE-jejx3)
--------------------------------------------------------
Before this floor learned about holds it could report only two outcomes:
STRANDED, or not. A branch that is unmerged BY DELIBERATE DECISION (a manager
issued an explicit do-not-merge hold) satisfies all four stranded predicates
IDENTICALLY to one that is unmerged BY ACCIDENT, so the floor filed a handoff
whose content — "nobody merged this, merge it" — was the EXACT INVERSE of the
standing instruction, and re-filed it every cadence once Chuck closed it.

A hold is now a FIRST-CLASS, DURABLE, MACHINE-READABLE state carried as
metadata ON THE WORK BEAD — never on the branch name, never in tmux traffic,
neither of which survives a pane restart (that non-durability IS the root
defect). Keying on the work bead means the hold SURVIVES A BRANCH RENAME or a
re-push under a new name: the bead already carries `branch` metadata
(SABLE-i5739), so re-pointing that field moves the hold with the work.

  hold        the reason (any non-empty value = HELD; this is the presence key)
  hold_by     who placed it        — an unowned hold is unreleasable after a recycle
  hold_since  ISO8601 timestamp    — so the hold's own AGE can be escalated
  hold_until  the release condition — "until what", the thing that prevents a
              hold decaying into a permanent quiet veto

  place:  bd update <work-bead> --sandbox \
            --set-metadata hold="<reason>" --set-metadata hold_by="<who>" \
            --set-metadata hold_since="<ISO8601>" --set-metadata hold_until="<condition>"
  lift:   bd update <work-bead> --sandbox --unset-metadata hold \
            --unset-metadata hold_by --unset-metadata hold_since --unset-metadata hold_until

A held branch is NEVER silently skipped. Silence is how the previous generation
of this bug worked (SABLE-2az2x: an instrument that cannot say "I could not
assess"), and a hold is WORSE than a strand in that direction because it is
SELF-SILENCING BY CONSTRUCTION — a forgotten strand is re-reported every cadence
until someone acts, while a forgotten hold suppresses the very report that would
surface it. So every cadence NAMES each held branch with by/since/until/reason,
and a hold that is stale (older than $SABLE_HOLD_STALE_DAYS, default 3), unowned,
undated, or carries no release condition is flagged NEEDING REVIEW in the summary.
A hold whose state could not be READ at all (the bead query failed) is its own
reported outcome — never folded into "not held", which would resume filing the
inverted handoff, and never into a clean summary.

STRANDED PREDICATE (a branch is stranded iff ALL FOUR hold, AND it is not HELD):
  1. origin's `wk-*` branch tip is NOT an ancestor of the integration branch
     (i.e. genuinely unmerged — `git merge-base --is-ancestor` exit 1).
  2. its work bead — resolved via STRUCTURED `branch` metadata first
     (SABLE-i5739; see find_work_bead_status), else an id parsed from the
     branch name, else a legacy prose `bd search` for pre-metadata branches
     — is closed or in_progress (real, done-or-in-flight work — never an
     experiment).
  3. NO open/in-progress `for-chuck` bead already NAMES the branch (the handoff
     was filed — by the hook OR a prior run of this tool). This is the
     idempotency key: our own filed bead names the branch, so a re-run finds it
     here and skips.
  4. the branch tip's push-age exceeds a threshold (default 10min, override via
     $SABLE_RECONCILE_AGE_MIN) — a settle window so a just-pushed branch whose
     hook handoff is still in flight is not raced.

Integration-branch identity is resolved through the SAME resolver the pre-push
hook and sable-merge-gate use post-SABLE-dtp1 (imported from bin/sable-merge-gate:
resolve_integration_branch) — never a hardcoded main/tmux-only, so ancestry is
judged against the branch this repo actually integrates onto.

TWO MORE NON-STRANDED OUTCOMES, CHECKED RIGHT AFTER HOLD (SABLE-4709h)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
A shift's worth of sixteen [RECONCILE] firings triaged to ZERO genuinely
stranded branches (SABLE-4709h). Two of the surviving healthy states were not
distinguishable from a real strand by ANY predicate above:

  IN-ACTIVE-REVISE    a live tmux worker pane is bound (via @sable_bead) to
                      this branch's work bead RIGHT NOW — a manager already
                      knows and a worker is on it. Checked via
                      branch_has_live_worker_pane against a fleet-wide pane
                      inventory (live_pane_bead_ids, reused from
                      bin/sable-worker-status — SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH, not
                      reimplemented). Fails OPEN to "no live pane found" when
                      tmux/pane context is unavailable at all (the
                      sable-reconcile-timer headless cadence runs with
                      neither by design), so a missing tmux server never
                      suppresses a genuine strand — it only means this ONE
                      extra discriminator sat out that cadence.

  REBASED-AND-LANDED  the branch's content is already at the spine under a
                      DIFFERENT sha (SABLE-z7gue). Predicate 1 above
                      (`git merge-base --is-ancestor`) asks "is this exact
                      SHA reachable", and a rebase changes every SHA, so a
                      fully-landed rebase copy answers 'not an ancestor'
                      IDENTICALLY to a genuinely stranded branch — and 'ask
                      both lanes' (SABLE-xw32f's remedy for the ambiguous
                      case) cannot separate them either, because every lane
                      truthfully answers 'not mine': the branch really is on
                      the spine, in nobody's hand. Checked via
                      branch_content_contained (`git cherry <upstream>
                      <head>`, the patch-id-equivalence relation) — contained
                      ONLY when EVERY commit unique to the branch is
                      patch-id-equivalent at the spine; a partially-landed
                      branch is conservatively left NOT-contained, since this
                      floor's own stranded remedy is a WRITE to the spine and
                      an indeterminate reading must never assert containment
                      it cannot fully back.

ACTION: for each stranded branch, file ONE `for-chuck,coord` bead whose title
names the branch. Chuck merges it from the pool exactly as he would a
hook-filed handoff.

PREVIEW-KICK LEG (SABLE-jd5fj.2 / S5 poll leg): independently of the stranded
predicate above, any origin `wk-*` branch that is genuinely unmerged (P1) and
past the settle window (P4) is a candidate for a MISSED push-time preview kick
(SABLE-jd5fj.1) — the hook may be unwired, may have raced the ref update, or
may have died mid-flight. This leg deliberately does NOT consult the work-bead
status (P2) or the for-chuck corpus (P3): a preview kick is a speculative CI
warm-up, not a merge handoff, so it fires regardless of whether a handoff bead
exists yet. Double-kick safety (hook vs. poll racing, or poll vs. poll) is
NEVER decided here — it is the SHARED IDEMPOTENCY KEY inside sable-merge-gate's
own `kick_preview` (preview_kick_ref, keyed on the (base_sha, branch_sha) pair),
which no-ops when a ref already exists for that exact pair. This leg is an
ADDITIONAL classification pass over the same branch list; it reads the four-
part stranded predicate below not at all and changes none of its outcomes.

BOUNDARIES (hard):
  * Files beads ONLY. NEVER merges, NEVER pushes code, NEVER deletes branches —
    the chuck-only push/merge lanes are preserved untouched.
  * Every `bd` WRITE is `--sandbox` (disables bd's Dolt auto-push, exactly as the
    hook does — SABLE-rq9k; Chuck's batched pull+push carries the bead to the
    shared remote, keeping dolt-push chuck-only).
  * `--dry-run` classifies + prints + files NOTHING + exits 0.

Environment seams (overridable; defaults are the production commands so the flow
is unit-testable without real git / bd / tmux):
  SABLE_RC_REPO   repo path (default $PWD)         SABLE_RC_GIT     (git)
  SABLE_RC_REMOTE remote name (origin)             SABLE_RC_BD      (bd)
                                                    SABLE_RC_TMUX    (tmux)
  SABLE_RECONCILE_AGE_MIN  push-age threshold, minutes (10)
  SABLE_HOLD_STALE_DAYS    a hold older than this is flagged for review (3)

Usage:
  sable-reconcile-handoffs [--repo PATH] [--remote NAME] [--age-min N]
                           [--hold-stale-days N] [--dry-run]
  sable-reconcile-handoffs --help

Exit codes:
  0  swept (beads filed, or dry-run, or nothing stranded)
  2  usage error
"""
from __future__ import annotations

import argparse
import importlib.util
import json
import os
import re
import subprocess
import sys
import time
from importlib.machinery import SourceFileLoader
from pathlib import Path

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reuse the merge-gate resolver + ref-qualifier — SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH.
# resolve_integration_branch is the SABLE-dtp1 resolver the pre-push hook and
# sable-merge-gate already agree on (git config sable.integrationBranch > .sable
# file > env > "main"); importing it (never re-implementing) guarantees this
# floor judges ancestry against the SAME integration branch the rest of the
# fleet targets. qualify_remote_ref carries the SABLE-92kc anti-ambiguity guard.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
_MG_PATH = Path(__file__).resolve().parent / "sable-merge-gate"
_MG_LOADER = SourceFileLoader("sable_merge_gate", str(_MG_PATH))
_MG_SPEC = importlib.util.spec_from_loader("sable_merge_gate", _MG_LOADER)
_smg = importlib.util.module_from_spec(_MG_SPEC)
_MG_LOADER.exec_module(_smg)

resolve_integration_branch = _smg.resolve_integration_branch
qualify_remote_ref = _smg.qualify_remote_ref
kick_preview = _smg.kick_preview

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reuse the fleet pane inventory — SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH (SABLE-4709h
# IN-ACTIVE-REVISE discriminator). sable-worker-status already parses
# `tmux list-panes` into {pane, bead, status, ...} records and already knows
# which bead ids have a currently-LIVE pane (live_beads); re-implementing that
# tab-format/parse contract here would drift the moment either file's pane
# tagging changes. Same SourceFileLoader technique as the sable-merge-gate
# import above.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
_WS_PATH = Path(__file__).resolve().parent / "sable-worker-status"
_WS_LOADER = SourceFileLoader("sable_worker_status", str(_WS_PATH))
_WS_SPEC = importlib.util.spec_from_loader("sable_worker_status", _WS_LOADER)
_sws = importlib.util.module_from_spec(_WS_SPEC)
_WS_LOADER.exec_module(_sws)

_ws_parse_fleet_panes = _sws.parse_fleet_panes
_ws_live_beads = _sws.live_beads
_ws_pane_format = _sws._FORMAT


# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pure predicates (unit-tested directly — no git/bd required)
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

def is_wk_branch(branch: str) -> bool:
    """Worker branches are `wk-*`. Only these are candidates — a manager's own
    push or the integration branch itself is never reconciled here."""
    return branch.startswith("wk-")


def ancestor_rc_is_unmerged(rc: int) -> bool:
    """Predicate 1. `git merge-base --is-ancestor <branch> <base>` exits 0 when
    the branch IS an ancestor (already merged) and 1 when it is NOT (unmerged).
    Only a clean rc==1 counts as unmerged — any other code (128 on a bad ref,
    etc.) is an UNRESOLVED classification, so we conservatively treat the branch
    as not-stranded rather than invent merge work off a git error."""
    return rc == 1


def work_bead_qualifies(status: str | None) -> bool:
    """Predicate 2. The branch's work bead must be closed (work finished) or
    in_progress (a landed-mid-flight worker) to count as real merge work. An
    absent bead (None), an open/blocked/deferred bead, or anything else does not
    qualify — the branch may be an abandoned experiment, and this floor never
    invents merge work no worker actually completed."""
    return status in ("closed", "in_progress")


def title_names_branch(title: str | None, branch: str) -> bool:
    """Predicate 3's core: does a `for-chuck` bead TITLE name this exact branch?
    Matched on a delimited-token boundary so `wk-foo` in a title does NOT match a
    bead about `wk-foobar` (branch chars are alnum plus - . / _). This is the
    idempotency key — our own filed title carries the branch, so a re-run sees it
    here and skips a duplicate."""
    if not title:
        return False
    pat = r"(?:^|[^\w./-])" + re.escape(branch) + r"(?:$|[^\w./-])"
    return re.search(pat, title) is not None


def branch_named_by_open_for_chuck(open_beads: list[dict] | None, branch: str) -> bool:
    """Predicate 3. True iff any open/in-progress `for-chuck` bead's title names
    the branch (a hook-filed handoff OR a prior reconciliation).

    open_beads is None when open_for_chuck_beads' query FAILED (corpus
    unknown, not legitimately empty) — treated as True (assume-named) so a
    transient bd failure suppresses filing rather than risking a duplicate.
    The conservative direction is deliberately the OPPOSITE of
    find_work_bead_status's metadata-query failure elsewhere in this file:
    there, an empty result would wrongly leave a branch un-strandable, so the
    safe fallback is to warn and keep going; here, an empty result IS the
    suppression signal reconcile() acts on, so the safe fallback is to
    assume-suppressed and skip this cadence."""
    if open_beads is None:
        return True
    return any(title_names_branch(b.get("title"), branch) for b in open_beads)


def age_exceeds_threshold(age_seconds: float, threshold_minutes: float) -> bool:
    """Predicate 4. Strict `>`: a branch AT the threshold is still inside the
    settle window and is left for the next sweep (mirrors is_orphan's strict-`>`
    in sable-merge-gate so the boundary is unambiguous)."""
    return age_seconds > threshold_minutes * 60.0


def preview_kick_eligible(rc: int, age_seconds: float | None,
                          threshold_minutes: float) -> tuple[bool, str]:
    """S5 poll-leg kick decision (SABLE-jd5fj.2): is this branch a candidate for
    a MISSED preview kick? Reuses predicate 1 (`ancestor_rc_is_unmerged`) and
    predicate 4 (`age_exceeds_threshold`) — the SAME pure checks the stranded
    predicate uses — but deliberately skips predicates 2/3 (work-bead status,
    for-chuck handoff already filed): a preview kick is a speculative CI
    warm-up, not a merge handoff, so it is eligible even for a branch with no
    work bead yet or one whose handoff bead already exists. Double-kick safety
    is NOT decided here — see `attempt_preview_kick`. Returns (eligible, reason)
    for the print trail, mirroring `classify_branch`'s shape."""
    if not ancestor_rc_is_unmerged(rc):
        return (False, f"merged-or-unresolvable(is-ancestor rc={rc})")
    if age_seconds is None:
        return (False, "age-unresolvable")
    if not age_exceeds_threshold(age_seconds, threshold_minutes):
        return (False, f"too-fresh({age_seconds:.0f}s <= {threshold_minutes}min settle)")
    return (True, "eligible-for-preview-kick")


# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HOLD: the first-class third outcome (SABLE-jejx3). Pure functions only — the
# hold lives in the WORK BEAD's metadata (see module docstring), so everything
# below operates on an already-fetched bead record and is unit-testable with no
# bd/git at all.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

HOLD_REASON_KEY = "hold"
HOLD_BY_KEY = "hold_by"
HOLD_SINCE_KEY = "hold_since"
HOLD_UNTIL_KEY = "hold_until"

# Sentinel for "the work bead could not be READ, so hold state is unknown".
# Deliberately NOT None (which means 'read fine, not held') — collapsing the two
# is exactly the mistake that files an inverted 'merge me' handoff for a branch
# that is in fact under a do-not-merge hold.
HOLD_UNKNOWN = "hold-state-unknown"

DEFAULT_HOLD_STALE_DAYS = 3.0


def hold_from_bead(bead: dict | None) -> dict | None:
    """The hold record carried by a work bead, or None when the bead is not
    held. Presence is keyed on a NON-EMPTY `hold` metadata value (the reason) —
    the other three fields are detail, and their ABSENCE is reported as a review
    flag rather than treated as a missing hold, so a sloppily-placed hold still
    protects the branch while being loudly incomplete."""
    if not isinstance(bead, dict):
        return None
    meta = bead.get("metadata")
    if not isinstance(meta, dict):
        return None
    reason = meta.get(HOLD_REASON_KEY)
    if not isinstance(reason, str) or not reason.strip():
        return None
    def _field(key: str) -> str | None:
        v = meta.get(key)
        return v.strip() if isinstance(v, str) and v.strip() else None
    return {
        "bead": bead.get("id"),
        "reason": reason.strip(),
        "by": _field(HOLD_BY_KEY),
        "since": _field(HOLD_SINCE_KEY),
        "until": _field(HOLD_UNTIL_KEY),
    }


def parse_hold_since(since: str | None) -> float | None:
    """Epoch seconds for an ISO8601 `hold_since` (a trailing `Z` is accepted —
    it is what bd and every SABLE timestamp writer emit). None when absent or
    unparseable; an unparseable date is treated the same as a missing one, i.e.
    the hold's age is UNKNOWN and that fact is flagged, never assumed fresh."""
    if not since:
        return None
    text = since.strip()
    if text.endswith("Z"):
        text = text[:-1] + "+00:00"
    try:
        from datetime import datetime
        dt = datetime.fromisoformat(text)
    except (ValueError, TypeError):
        return None
    if dt.tzinfo is None:
        from datetime import timezone
        dt = dt.replace(tzinfo=timezone.utc)
    return dt.timestamp()


def hold_age_days(hold: dict, now: float) -> float | None:
    """Age of the hold in days, or None when `hold_since` is missing/unparseable."""
    ts = parse_hold_since(hold.get("since"))
    if ts is None:
        return None
    return max(0.0, (now - ts) / 86400.0)


def hold_review_flags(hold: dict, now: float, stale_days: float) -> list[str]:
    """Why this hold itself needs a human look. A hold suppresses the report
    that would otherwise surface its branch, so an un-reviewable hold decays
    into a permanent quiet veto that outlives everyone who knew why it was
    placed — these flags are what make that decay LOUD instead of silent."""
    flags: list[str] = []
    if not hold.get("by"):
        flags.append("UNOWNED(no hold_by — nobody can release it)")
    if not hold.get("until"):
        flags.append("NO-RELEASE-CONDITION(no hold_until — cannot expire)")
    age = hold_age_days(hold, now)
    if age is None:
        flags.append("AGE-UNKNOWN(no parseable hold_since)")
    elif age > stale_days:
        flags.append(f"STALE({age:.1f}d > {stale_days:g}d)")
    return flags


def describe_hold(hold: dict, now: float, stale_days: float) -> str:
    """The per-cadence HELD line. Carries all four fields chuck required —
    held, BY WHOM, SINCE WHEN, UNTIL WHAT — plus the review flags, so a fresh
    manager reading one sweep's output has everything needed to either respect
    or release the hold without any surviving tmux context."""
    age = hold_age_days(hold, now)
    age_txt = f"{age:.1f}d" if age is not None else "age-unknown"
    flags = hold_review_flags(hold, now, stale_days)
    flag_txt = f" [NEEDS REVIEW: {'; '.join(flags)}]" if flags else ""
    return (
        f"HELD — do NOT merge (deliberate, not stranded); "
        f"by={hold.get('by') or 'UNKNOWN'} "
        f"since={hold.get('since') or 'UNKNOWN'} ({age_txt}) "
        f"until={hold.get('until') or 'UNSTATED'} "
        f"reason={hold['reason']}"
        f"{flag_txt}"
    )


def hold_lift_hint(hold: dict) -> str:
    """The exact command that releases this hold. Printed with every held
    branch so releasing one never requires reading this source file."""
    bead = hold.get("bead") or "<work-bead>"
    return (f"to lift: bd update {bead} --sandbox --unset-metadata hold "
            f"--unset-metadata hold_by --unset-metadata hold_since "
            f"--unset-metadata hold_until")


_BEAD_ID_RE = re.compile(r"[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9]*-[A-Za-z0-9]+(?:\.[0-9]+)*")


def parse_bead_id(branch: str) -> str | None:
    """Best-effort bead id embedded in a branch name. Strips a leading `wk-`
    worktree prefix, then returns the first bead-id-shaped token (e.g.
    `wk-SABLE-jfg6.3` -> `SABLE-jfg6.3`). Returns None when nothing id-shaped
    remains. A token that isn't a real bead id just makes the downstream
    `bd show` miss and fall through to `bd search` — harmless."""
    core = branch
    for pfx in ("wk-", "worktree-"):
        if core.startswith(pfx):
            core = core[len(pfx):]
            break
    m = _BEAD_ID_RE.search(core)
    return m.group(0) if m else None


def status_from_show_json(text: str) -> str | None:
    """Status out of a `bd show <id> --json` payload — accepts either a bare
    object or a single-element list (bd returns a list), None on any parse
    failure or empty result."""
    try:
        d = json.loads(text)
    except (json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError):
        return None
    if isinstance(d, list):
        d = d[0] if d else None
    return d.get("status") if isinstance(d, dict) else None


def record_from_show_json(text: str) -> dict | None:
    """The WHOLE bead record out of a `bd show <id> --json` payload (bare object
    or single-element list). The record — not just its status — is what carries
    the hold metadata (SABLE-jejx3), so resolution returns the object and the
    status accessors read from it."""
    try:
        d = json.loads(text)
    except (json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError):
        return None
    if isinstance(d, list):
        d = d[0] if d else None
    return d if isinstance(d, dict) else None


def all_records_from_search_json(text: str) -> list[dict]:
    """EVERY record in a `bd list`/`bd search --json` payload, in payload order.

    More than one bead can legitimately carry the same `branch` metadata (an
    observation/scratch bead filed against the same branch as the real work
    bead — this is not hypothetical; it is what the live corpus looks like).
    Predicate 2 only needs one status, but HOLD resolution must see them ALL:
    if any joined bead is held, the branch is held, and letting an arbitrary
    payload ordering decide would silently drop a hold and resume filing the
    inverted 'merge me' handoff — the exact defect this floor is fixing."""
    try:
        d = json.loads(text)
    except (json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError):
        return []
    if isinstance(d, dict):
        d = [d]
    return [r for r in d if isinstance(r, dict)] if isinstance(d, list) else []


def first_record_from_search_json(text: str) -> dict | None:
    """The first whole record in a `bd list`/`bd search --json` payload (a
    list), None if empty/unparseable. Record-level counterpart of
    first_status_from_search_json."""
    try:
        d = json.loads(text)
    except (json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError):
        return None
    if isinstance(d, dict):
        d = [d]
    if isinstance(d, list) and d and isinstance(d[0], dict):
        return d[0]
    return None


def first_status_from_search_json(text: str) -> str | None:
    """Status of the first hit in a `bd search --json` payload (a list), None if
    empty/unparseable."""
    try:
        d = json.loads(text)
    except (json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError):
        return None
    if isinstance(d, dict):
        d = [d]
    if isinstance(d, list) and d and isinstance(d[0], dict):
        return d[0].get("status")
    return None


def reconcile_bead_title(branch: str) -> str:
    """The filed bead's title. The branch name is the idempotency key
    (predicate 3 / title_names_branch), so it MUST appear here, delimited."""
    return f"[RECONCILE] stranded merge: {branch} — no for-chuck handoff on record"


def reconcile_bead_description(branch: str, work_status: str | None) -> str:
    return (
        "Filed by sable-reconcile-handoffs (SABLE-jfg6.3 / D3), the pull-based "
        "reconciliation floor: this branch is pushed to origin and UNMERGED, its "
        f"work bead is {work_status}, and NO for-chuck bead named it — the "
        "push-based post-push-merge-notify handoff never reached Chuck (research "
        "F4 notify-miss). Treat exactly as a hook-filed handoff.\n"
        f"\nBranch: {branch}\n"
        "\n## Acceptance Criteria\n"
        "- Inspect the branch on origin and merge into the integration branch "
        "(or hold with reason)\n"
        "- Close this bead on merge\n"
    )


# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Command plumbing (env-seam overridable — mirrors sable-merge-gate)
#
# SABLE-6sdpx AUDIT: every _git/_bd call in this file runs with check=False.
# All but one already inspect .returncode right at (or immediately after) the
# call site and fall through to the CONSERVATIVE branch on failure — merged-
# or-unresolvable stays not-stranded (branch_ancestor_rc / ancestor_rc_is_
# unmerged), an unresolvable age/status returns None and the branch is left
# for the next sweep (branch_tip_age_seconds, find_work_bead_status), and a
# failed bead write is a loud caller-side WARNING (file_for_chuck_bead, see
# reconcile()). The one exception — the reconcile()-level `git fetch --prune`
# refresh, which discarded its CompletedProcess outright — is fixed below.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

def _tool(env_name: str, default: str) -> list[str]:
    return os.environ.get(env_name, default).split()


def _run(argv: list[str], *, cwd: str, check: bool = False) -> subprocess.CompletedProcess:
    return subprocess.run(
        argv, cwd=cwd, text=True, check=check,
        stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,
    )


def _git(repo: str, *args: str, check: bool = False) -> subprocess.CompletedProcess:
    return _run(_tool("SABLE_RC_GIT", "git") + list(args), cwd=repo, check=check)


def _bd(repo: str, *args: str, check: bool = False) -> subprocess.CompletedProcess:
    return _run(_tool("SABLE_RC_BD", "bd") + list(args), cwd=repo, check=check)


def _tmux(repo: str, *args: str, check: bool = False) -> subprocess.CompletedProcess:
    return _run(_tool("SABLE_RC_TMUX", "tmux") + list(args), cwd=repo, check=check)


# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Systems-of-record queries (git + beads, behind the pure predicates)
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

def list_origin_wk_branches(repo: str, remote: str) -> list[str]:
    """Bare `wk-*` branch names published on <remote>, from the local
    remote-tracking refs (caller fetch --prune's first). The remote/ prefix is
    stripped so downstream qualify_remote_ref sees a bare name."""
    cp = _git(repo, "for-each-ref", "--format=%(refname:short)",
              f"refs/remotes/{remote}/wk-*", check=False)
    if cp.returncode != 0:
        return []
    out: list[str] = []
    prefix = f"{remote}/"
    for line in cp.stdout.splitlines():
        short = line.strip()
        if not short:
            continue
        name = short[len(prefix):] if short.startswith(prefix) else short
        if is_wk_branch(name):
            out.append(name)
    return out


def branch_ancestor_rc(repo: str, remote: str, branch: str, integration_branch: str) -> int:
    """`git merge-base --is-ancestor origin/<branch> origin/<integration>` return
    code (0 merged, 1 unmerged, other error). Both refs fully qualified via the
    reused qualify_remote_ref anti-ambiguity guard."""
    branch_ref = qualify_remote_ref(remote, branch)
    base_ref = qualify_remote_ref(remote, integration_branch)
    cp = _git(repo, "merge-base", "--is-ancestor", branch_ref, base_ref, check=False)
    return cp.returncode


def branch_tip_age_seconds(repo: str, remote: str, branch: str, now: float) -> float | None:
    """Push-age proxy: (now - committer date of origin/<branch> tip). The commit
    time is the only push-age signal cheaply available from a fetched
    remote-tracking ref (mirrors sable-merge-gate sweep's committerdate keying).
    None on any resolution failure — an unresolvable age fails predicate 4."""
    ref = qualify_remote_ref(remote, branch)
    cp = _git(repo, "log", "-1", "--format=%ct", ref, check=False)
    if cp.returncode != 0:
        return None
    try:
        return now - float(cp.stdout.strip())
    except ValueError:
        return None


def find_work_bead_records(repo: str, branch: str) -> tuple[list[dict], bool]:
    """ALL work-bead records joined to the branch, plus whether resolution was
    READABLE.

    Returns (records, resolved_ok). `resolved_ok` is False only when the
    resolution machinery ITSELF failed (the structured metadata query exited
    nonzero and no fallback produced a record) — i.e. "we could not read", as
    opposed to "we read fine and there is no bead" (None, True). Predicate 2
    (status) can safely collapse those two, because an unresolvable status
    conservatively leaves the branch not-stranded either way. HOLD state cannot:
    collapsing unreadable into not-held is precisely how the floor would resume
    filing an inverted 'merge me' handoff against a held branch, so
    find_work_bead_hold keeps the distinction and reports it.

    Resolution order is unchanged from SABLE-i5739 — see find_work_bead_status
    for the full rationale of why structured metadata is primary. What DID
    change (SABLE-jejx3) is arity: the metadata leg returns EVERY joined bead
    rather than only the first, because a hold on any of them holds the branch
    (see all_records_from_search_json)."""
    resolvable_failure = False
    cp = _bd(repo, "list", "--status", "all",
             "--metadata-field", f"branch={branch}", "--json", check=False)
    if cp.returncode != 0:
        resolvable_failure = True
        print(f"sable-reconcile-handoffs: WARNING branch-metadata resolution "
              f"failed for {branch} (bd list exit {cp.returncode}) — falling "
              f"back to legacy resolution, NOT treating this as "
              f"no-qualifying-bead: {cp.stdout.strip()}", file=sys.stderr)
    else:
        recs = [r for r in all_records_from_search_json(cp.stdout)
                if r.get("status") is not None]
        if recs:
            return (recs, True)

    bead_id = parse_bead_id(branch)
    if bead_id:
        cp = _bd(repo, "show", bead_id, "--json", check=False)
        if cp.returncode == 0:
            rec = record_from_show_json(cp.stdout)
            if rec is not None and rec.get("status") is not None:
                return ([rec], True)

    cp = _bd(repo, "search", branch, "--status", "all", "--json", check=False)
    if cp.returncode == 0:
        rec = first_record_from_search_json(cp.stdout)
        if rec is not None:
            return ([rec], True)
        return ([], not resolvable_failure)
    return ([], not resolvable_failure)


def find_work_bead(repo: str, branch: str) -> tuple[dict | None, bool]:
    """The branch's PRIMARY work-bead record (the first joined bead) plus
    whether resolution was readable — the single-record view predicate 2 uses."""
    recs, ok = find_work_bead_records(repo, branch)
    return (recs[0] if recs else None, ok)


def find_work_bead_hold(repo: str, branch: str) -> dict | str | None:
    """The branch's HOLD state (SABLE-jejx3). Three distinct outcomes, never two:

      * a hold record  — the branch is deliberately held; do NOT file, DO report
      * None           — the work bead read fine and carries no hold
      * HOLD_UNKNOWN   — the bead could not be read at all, so 'held' can be
                         neither confirmed nor ruled out. Reported as its own
                         outcome; the floor does not file against it, because
                         filing an INVERTED handoff for a genuinely held branch
                         is unrecoverable-by-automation in a way that deferring
                         one cadence of a real strand is not — and unlike a
                         silent skip, this one says so in the summary.

    The hold is read from the WORK BEAD, so it survives a branch rename: the
    bead's `branch` metadata is re-pointed and the hold travels with it.

    EVERY bead joined to the branch is consulted, not just the first: a hold on
    any of them holds the branch. Ordering must never decide whether a hold is
    honoured (the live corpus routinely has an observation bead joined to the
    same branch as the real work bead, and it can sort first)."""
    records, ok = find_work_bead_records(repo, branch)
    if not ok:
        return HOLD_UNKNOWN
    for rec in records:
        hold = hold_from_bead(rec)
        if hold is not None:
            return hold
    return None


def find_work_bead_status(repo: str, branch: str) -> str | None:
    """The branch's work-bead status (predicate 2). Resolution order
    (SABLE-i5739 — prose-search closed as the primary resolver):

      1. STRUCTURED metadata: `bd list --metadata-field branch=<branch>
         --status all --json` — an EXACT key/value match against the
         `branch` metadata field sable-spawn-worker now writes on every
         bead at dispatch time (see tag_branch_metadata there). This is the
         PRIMARY path and, once a bead carries the field, the ONLY path
         consulted: an unrelated bead whose title/description merely
         mentions the branch text can never win here (closes mode b — WRONG
         SUCCESS), and the answer cannot drift as such beads accumulate
         later (closes mode c — DRIFT), because bead-carried metadata
         identity, not prose content, is what is being matched. A branch
         whose bead text never names it at all still resolves correctly
         (closes mode a — SILENT FAILURE), since this path never reads
         title/description.
      2. Embedded bead id in the branch name (`bd show`) — a pure
         convenience for a branch that happens to carry a bead id token;
         unaffected by this change.
      3. LEGACY prose `bd search` fallback — reached ONLY when neither of
         the above resolves anything, i.e. a branch dispatched BEFORE the
         metadata field existed. Prose-fragile by construction (the exact
         defect this bead closes), but every branch dispatched going
         forward always carries the metadata field, so this path retires
         naturally as old branches merge or expire; it is kept only so
         already-pushed pre-fix branches are not made WORSE (silently
         un-strandable) than they were before.

    A failed metadata query (nonzero bd exit) is NEVER silently folded into
    "no bead" — falling through unresolved-but-loud would leave the branch
    un-strandable with zero operator signal, one of the exact modes this
    bead fixes for the metadata path itself. It's printed as a loud WARNING
    (mirroring reconcile()'s git-fetch-failure WARNING) so 'nothing
    stranded' (query ran clean, found nothing) is never confused with
    'resolution failed' (the query itself is broken) — dispatch note #8.

    Thin accessor over find_work_bead (SABLE-jejx3 moved the resolution
    itself there so the SAME resolver serves both status and hold — one
    resolution order, one place to change it)."""
    bead, _ = find_work_bead(repo, branch)
    return bead.get("status") if isinstance(bead, dict) else None


def open_for_chuck_beads(repo: str) -> list[dict] | None:
    """Open + in-progress `for-chuck` beads (predicate 3's corpus). in_progress
    included so a handoff Chuck has already STARTED still suppresses a duplicate.

    Returns None — NOT [] — when the query itself failed (nonzero bd exit or
    unparseable JSON), so a transient bd failure is never indistinguishable
    from 'genuinely zero open handoffs'. Unlike find_work_bead_status's
    metadata query (SABLE-i5739), where a silent 'no bead' makes a branch
    un-strandable and the safe fallback is to WARN-AND-CONTINUE, an empty
    result HERE is predicate 3's suppression signal: reconcile() files a
    for-chuck bead only when this corpus does NOT already name the branch.
    Folding query-failure into empty would make the sweep FILE A DUPLICATE
    into chuck's queue — not self-correcting, unlike skipping one cadence."""
    cp = _bd(repo, "list", "--status", "open,in_progress",
             "--label", "for-chuck", "--json", check=False)
    if cp.returncode != 0:
        print(f"sable-reconcile-handoffs: WARNING for-chuck bead query failed "
              f"(bd list exit {cp.returncode}) — treating the corpus as "
              f"UNKNOWN, not empty, so this cadence skips filing rather than "
              f"risk a duplicate handoff: {cp.stdout.strip()}", file=sys.stderr)
        return None
    try:
        d = json.loads(cp.stdout)
    except (json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError):
        print(f"sable-reconcile-handoffs: WARNING for-chuck bead query "
              f"returned unparseable JSON — treating the corpus as UNKNOWN, "
              f"not empty, so this cadence skips filing rather than risk a "
              f"duplicate handoff", file=sys.stderr)
        return None
    return [b for b in d if isinstance(b, dict)] if isinstance(d, list) else []


def file_for_chuck_bead(repo: str, branch: str, work_status: str | None) -> subprocess.CompletedProcess:
    """File ONE for-chuck,coord bead naming the branch. ALWAYS --sandbox
    (SABLE-rq9k: local-only write, no Dolt auto-push — the chuck-only push lane
    stays intact)."""
    return _bd(
        repo, "create", "--sandbox",
        "--title", reconcile_bead_title(branch),
        "--type=task", "--priority=2",
        "--labels=for-chuck,coord",
        "--description", reconcile_bead_description(branch, work_status),
        check=False,
    )


def attempt_preview_kick(repo: str, remote: str, branch: str,
                         integration_branch: str) -> tuple[bool, str]:
    """Kick the SABLE-jd5fj.1 preview entrypoint for a branch whose push-time
    kick may have been missed (hook unwired, race, mid-flight crash). Delegates
    entirely to sable-merge-gate's `kick_preview`, which is ALREADY idempotent
    on the shared `preview_kick_ref` key (base_sha, branch_sha) — a ref that
    exists because the hook (or a prior poll run) already kicked it is a no-op
    read inside `kick_preview`, never a rebuild or a second CI trigger. That
    single shared key — not any dedup logic here — is what makes a hook-kicked
    and a poll-kicked preview mutually suppressing in EITHER race order (the
    columbo IDEMPOTENCY OVERLAP boundary case). Never raises: a missed or
    failed kick is a lost optimization, not a reconcile failure, so promote
    still builds its own preview later if this attempt never landed one."""
    try:
        rc = kick_preview(branch, integration_branch, repo, remote)
        return (rc == 0, "kick-ok(kicked-or-already-kicked)" if rc == 0 else f"kick-exit-{rc}")
    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001 — a kick failure must never abort the sweep
        return (False, f"kick-error:{exc}")


def live_pane_bead_ids(repo: str) -> set[str]:
    """Bead ids with a currently-LIVE tmux worker pane bound to them (SABLE-4709h
    IN-ACTIVE-REVISE discriminator — "1 IN ACTIVE REVISE — a live worker pane,
    bounced by its own manager (SABLE-660hy)" was one of sixteen false-positive
    firings a plain tip/handoff-bead classifier cannot tell apart from a real
    strand). A live pane tagged with a bead via @sable_bead means a manager
    already knows this branch's work is being actively reworked right now —
    filing a stranded handoff against it repeats the exact 'ask every lane,
    get a truthful not-mine from each' trap this floor exists to avoid, except
    here the answer WAS available, just not from bd or git.

    Fails OPEN to an EMPTY set — NEVER raises, never treated as unknown-and-
    suppress. sable-reconcile-timer's headless cadence deliberately runs with
    NO tmux server and NO pane context at all (SABLE-jd5fj.2 S5 walk-away
    path; see test_S5_U1_timer_once_catches_notify_miss_without_tmux_or_pane_
    context), so 'could not enumerate panes' must never make the floor stop
    reporting real strands the way an unreadable hold or for-chuck corpus
    does — it only means this ONE extra discriminator is unavailable this
    cadence; every other predicate still runs unchanged."""
    try:
        cp = _tmux(repo, "list-panes", "-a", "-F", _ws_pane_format, check=False)
    except (OSError, FileNotFoundError):
        return set()
    if cp.returncode != 0:
        return set()
    return _ws_live_beads(_ws_parse_fleet_panes(cp.stdout))


def branch_has_live_worker_pane(repo: str, branch: str, live_bead_ids: set[str]) -> bool:
    """True iff ANY bead joined to `branch` (every record find_work_bead_records
    resolves, plus a bead id embedded in the branch name itself — the same two
    sources the hold check consults) has a currently-live pane. Checked against
    the whole joined set, not just the primary work bead, for the same reason
    find_work_bead_hold does: an observation/scratch bead can be joined to the
    same branch and sort first, and a live pane on THAT bead is just as much
    in-active-revise as one on the primary."""
    if not live_bead_ids:
        return False
    records, _ = find_work_bead_records(repo, branch)
    ids = {r.get("id") for r in records if isinstance(r, dict) and r.get("id")}
    embedded = parse_bead_id(branch)
    if embedded:
        ids.add(embedded)
    return bool(ids & live_bead_ids)


def branch_content_contained(repo: str, remote: str, branch: str,
                             integration_branch: str) -> tuple[bool, str]:
    """SABLE-z7gue: does `branch`'s content already exist at the spine under a
    DIFFERENT sha — a REBASED-AND-LANDED branch whose original ref may still
    be a tip-keyed corpse (or, per z7gue's actual instance, whose ref was
    already deleted but a preview/tag/other tip-keyed probe still finds the
    pre-rebase commit). Ancestry (predicate 1, `git merge-base --is-ancestor`)
    is exactly wrong for this: it asks "is this exact SHA reachable from the
    integration branch", and a rebase changes every SHA, so a fully-landed
    rebase copy answers 'not an ancestor' IDENTICALLY to a genuinely stranded
    branch. 'ask both lanes' (SABLE-xw32f's remedy) cannot separate them
    either: every lane truthfully answers 'not mine', because the branch
    really is in nobody's hand — it is on the spine.

    Uses `git cherry <upstream> <head>` (z7gue's own suggested mechanism):
    each commit unique to `branch` is prefixed '-' when a patch-id-equivalent
    commit already exists in `integration_branch` (the exact rebase-copy
    relation), '+' when it is genuinely new. Returns (fully_contained, detail).

    fully_contained is True ONLY when EVERY commit unique to the branch is
    patch-id-equivalent — a PARTIALLY landed branch (some commits landed, some
    not) is conservatively left NOT-contained, per the module's stated
    default: this floor's stranded verdict is the ONE place its own remedy is
    a WRITE to the spine (re-merge), so an indeterminate/partial reading must
    fall through to the ordinary predicates rather than assert containment it
    cannot fully back. An unresolvable `git cherry` (nonzero exit) or an EMPTY
    result (ancestry already said unmerged, so a genuinely empty cherry
    listing would mean the two views disagree) both return NOT-contained —
    never invent a landed verdict off a failed or ambiguous comparison."""
    branch_ref = qualify_remote_ref(remote, branch)
    base_ref = qualify_remote_ref(remote, integration_branch)
    cp = _git(repo, "cherry", base_ref, branch_ref, check=False)
    if cp.returncode != 0:
        return (False, f"patch-id-check-unresolvable(git cherry exit {cp.returncode})")
    lines = [ln for ln in cp.stdout.splitlines() if ln.strip()]
    if not lines:
        return (False, "patch-id-check-empty(no unique commits found)")
    new_commits = [ln for ln in lines if ln.startswith("+")]
    if new_commits:
        return (False, f"patch-id-partial({len(lines) - len(new_commits)} of "
                        f"{len(lines)} commit(s) patch-id-equivalent at the spine)")
    return (True, f"content-contained({len(lines)} commit(s) patch-id-equivalent "
                  f"at the spine under a different sha)")


# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Classification + orchestration
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------

def classify_branch(repo: str, remote: str, branch: str, integration_branch: str,
                    open_beads: list[dict] | None, threshold_minutes: float,
                    now: float, hold: dict | str | None = None,
                    stale_days: float = DEFAULT_HOLD_STALE_DAYS,
                    live_bead_ids: set[str] | None = None) -> tuple[bool, str, str | None]:
    """Apply the stranded predicate to ONE branch. Returns (is_stranded, reason,
    work_status). Cheap/pure checks first; the bead-status lookup (a subprocess)
    runs only after ancestry + for-chuck rule the branch in as a live candidate.

    `hold` (SABLE-jejx3) is the branch's already-resolved hold state — a hold
    record, None for not-held, or HOLD_UNKNOWN for unreadable (see
    find_work_bead_hold). It is checked immediately after ancestry, BEFORE the
    remaining stranded predicates, because a deliberately-held branch satisfies
    every one of them and the handoff they would produce says the exact
    OPPOSITE of the standing instruction. It is resolved by the caller rather
    than here so reconcile() can also report it, held branches being a reported
    outcome and never a silent skip. Defaults to None so every pre-existing
    call site keeps its exact prior behavior.

    `live_bead_ids` (SABLE-4709h) is the whole fleet's set of bead ids with a
    currently-live tmux pane, resolved ONCE per sweep by the caller (mirrors
    `open_beads`) and checked immediately after HOLD, before predicate 3 — a
    branch actively being reworked in a live pane is exactly as much a
    reported non-strand as a held one, and for the same reason: filing a
    handoff would say the opposite of what is actually happening. Defaults to
    None (treated as empty) so every pre-existing call site keeps its exact
    prior behavior.

    Content-containment (SABLE-z7gue) is checked right after that, still
    ahead of predicate 3: a branch whose commits are already patch-id-
    equivalent at the spine under a different sha is REBASED-AND-LANDED, not
    stranded, regardless of what the for-chuck corpus or work-bead status say
    — tip-containment (predicate 1 above) cannot see this, because a rebase
    changes every SHA."""
    rc = branch_ancestor_rc(repo, remote, branch, integration_branch)
    if not ancestor_rc_is_unmerged(rc):
        return (False, f"merged-or-unresolvable(is-ancestor rc={rc})", None)

    if hold == HOLD_UNKNOWN:
        return (False,
                "hold-state-unknown(work bead unreadable) — NOT filing: cannot "
                "rule out a deliberate do-not-merge hold", None)
    if isinstance(hold, dict):
        return (False, describe_hold(hold, now, stale_days), None)

    if branch_has_live_worker_pane(repo, branch, live_bead_ids or set()):
        return (False, "in-active-revise(a live worker pane is bound to this "
                        "branch's work bead)", None)

    contained, contained_detail = branch_content_contained(
        repo, remote, branch, integration_branch)
    if contained:
        return (False, f"landed-under-different-sha({contained_detail})", None)

    if branch_named_by_open_for_chuck(open_beads, branch):
        return (False, "handoff-already-on-record", None)

    status = find_work_bead_status(repo, branch)
    if not work_bead_qualifies(status):
        return (False, f"no-qualifying-work-bead(status={status})", status)

    age = branch_tip_age_seconds(repo, remote, branch, now)
    if age is None:
        return (False, "age-unresolvable", status)
    if not age_exceeds_threshold(age, threshold_minutes):
        return (False, f"too-fresh({age:.0f}s <= {threshold_minutes}min settle)", status)

    return (True, "STRANDED", status)


def reconcile(repo: str, remote: str, threshold_minutes: float, dry_run: bool,
              stale_days: float = DEFAULT_HOLD_STALE_DAYS) -> int:
    integration_branch = resolve_integration_branch(repo)
    # Refresh remote-tracking refs so ancestry + age read origin's current
    # truth. SABLE-6sdpx: git exits nonzero here on a real network/auth
    # failure and NOT on "nothing new to fetch" (that is still exit 0), so a
    # nonzero rc always means the refresh did not happen — never a
    # legitimate no-op. A failed refresh is not fatal (the sweep can still
    # run stale-but-real local refs and will fetch again next cadence), but
    # it must be LOUD: silently classifying against stale refs looks
    # identical to a healthy sweep otherwise.
    fetch_cp = _git(repo, "fetch", remote, "--prune", check=False)
    if fetch_cp.returncode != 0:
        print(f"sable-reconcile-handoffs: WARNING git fetch {remote} --prune "
              f"failed (exit {fetch_cp.returncode}) — classifying against "
              f"POSSIBLY STALE remote-tracking refs: {fetch_cp.stdout.strip()}",
              file=sys.stderr)

    branches = list_origin_wk_branches(repo, remote)
    open_beads = open_for_chuck_beads(repo)
    corpus_unknown = open_beads is None
    # SABLE-4709h: resolved ONCE per sweep, mirroring open_beads — a pane
    # enumeration per branch would be wasteful and (worse) could observe a
    # different fleet snapshot for different branches in the same cadence.
    live_bead_ids = live_pane_bead_ids(repo)
    now = time.time()

    mode = "DRY-RUN" if dry_run else "reconcile"
    print(f"sable-reconcile-handoffs [{mode}]: integration branch '{integration_branch}', "
          f"{len(branches)} origin wk-* branch(es), age threshold {threshold_minutes}min")

    stranded: list[tuple[str, str | None]] = []
    held: list[tuple[str, dict]] = []
    hold_unreadable: list[str] = []
    unassessed = 0
    kick_candidates = 0
    kicked = 0
    for br in branches:
        if br == integration_branch:
            continue

        # Preview-kick leg (SABLE-jd5fj.2 / S5 poll leg): an ADDITIONAL,
        # independent classification pass — reuses P1/P4 only (see
        # preview_kick_eligible), never touches the stranded predicate below.
        rc = branch_ancestor_rc(repo, remote, br, integration_branch)
        kick_age = (branch_tip_age_seconds(repo, remote, br, now)
                    if ancestor_rc_is_unmerged(rc) else None)
        kick_eligible, kick_reason = preview_kick_eligible(rc, kick_age, threshold_minutes)
        if kick_eligible:
            kick_candidates += 1
            if dry_run:
                print(f"  {br}: [dry-run] would attempt preview-kick ({kick_reason})")
            else:
                ok, detail = attempt_preview_kick(repo, remote, br, integration_branch)
                if ok:
                    kicked += 1
                print(f"  {br}: preview-kick {detail}")

        # HOLD state (SABLE-jejx3) — resolved here, not inside classify_branch,
        # because a held branch is a REPORTED outcome, not a suppressed one, so
        # the sweep needs the record itself. Resolved only for branches that
        # cleared P1: a merged branch is nobody's concern, held or not.
        hold = (find_work_bead_hold(repo, br)
                if ancestor_rc_is_unmerged(rc) else None)

        is_stranded, reason, status = classify_branch(
            repo, remote, br, integration_branch, open_beads, threshold_minutes,
            now, hold, stale_days, live_bead_ids)
        print(f"  {br}: {reason}")
        if isinstance(hold, dict):
            held.append((br, hold))
        elif hold == HOLD_UNKNOWN:
            hold_unreadable.append(br)
        if is_stranded:
            stranded.append((br, status))
        elif corpus_unknown and reason == "handoff-already-on-record":
            # predicate 3 assumed-named this branch only because the for-chuck
            # corpus query failed (branch_named_by_open_for_chuck(None, ...) is
            # unconditionally True) — its real strandedness was never actually
            # checked. Count it so the summary can say so instead of reading
            # identical to a fleet where nothing is stranded.
            unassessed += 1

    filed = 0
    for br, status in stranded:
        if dry_run:
            print(f"  [dry-run] would file for-chuck bead for {br} (work bead {status})")
            continue
        cp = file_for_chuck_bead(repo, br, status)
        if cp.returncode == 0:
            filed += 1
            print(f"  filed for-chuck bead for stranded branch {br}")
        else:
            print(f"  WARNING: could not file for-chuck bead for {br} "
                  f"(bd exit {cp.returncode}): {cp.stdout.strip()}")

    # SABLE-jejx3: HELD branches are RE-REPORTED, loudly, every single cadence.
    # This recap exists in addition to the per-branch line above because a hold
    # is self-silencing by construction — it suppresses the strand report that
    # would otherwise keep its branch visible — so the one thing this floor must
    # never do is let a hold quietly become permanent. Naming every held branch
    # with by/since/until/reason and the exact lift command makes a forgotten
    # hold as visible as a forgotten strand.
    review_needed = 0
    if held:
        print(f"  --- HELD BRANCHES ({len(held)}) — deliberate, do NOT merge; "
              f"re-reported every cadence by design ---")
        for br, hold in held:
            flags = hold_review_flags(hold, now, stale_days)
            if flags:
                review_needed += 1
            print(f"  HELD {br}: {describe_hold(hold, now, stale_days)}")
            print(f"       {hold_lift_hint(hold)}")
    for br in hold_unreadable:
        print(f"  HOLD-STATE UNREADABLE {br}: work bead could not be read — "
              f"neither held nor not-held could be established, so nothing was "
              f"filed for it this cadence")

    # SABLE-2az2x: an UNKNOWN for-chuck corpus makes the reconciler assume-named
    # (skip-filing) for every unmerged branch it sees, cadence after cadence, if
    # the underlying query failure is PERSISTENT rather than transient — and the
    # summary below would otherwise print the exact same "0 stranded, 0 filed"
    # a genuinely healthy fleet prints. That is indistinguishable-from-healthy,
    # which is worse than the duplicate handoff the suppression prevents (a
    # duplicate is visible and reconcilable; a silently-stopped floor is not).
    # Suppression itself stays unbounded here (per-cadence WARNING already
    # covers the transient case) — this only makes the SUMMARY say so.
    corpus_note = (
        f" (CORPUS UNREADABLE — suppression active, {unassessed} branch(es) unassessed)"
        if corpus_unknown else ""
    )
    # SABLE-jejx3: the summary carries the held count too — the three outcomes
    # this floor can now report are STRANDED, HELD, and could-not-assess, and a
    # summary that named only the first would be the two-state instrument this
    # bead exists to retire. Held branches are NAMED, not just counted, so one
    # grep of the summary line answers "what is deliberately not merging".
    held_note = ""
    if held:
        names = ", ".join(br for br, _ in held)
        held_note = f" [{names}]"
        if review_needed:
            held_note += f" ({review_needed} NEEDING REVIEW)"
    if hold_unreadable:
        held_note += (f"; {len(hold_unreadable)} branch(es) with UNREADABLE "
                      f"hold state [{', '.join(hold_unreadable)}]")
    held_summary = f"{len(held)} held branch(es){held_note}"

    if dry_run:
        print(f"sable-reconcile-handoffs [DRY-RUN]: {len(stranded)} stranded branch(es) "
              f"classified, 0 filed (dry-run){corpus_note}; {held_summary}; "
              f"{kick_candidates} preview-kick candidate(s), 0 kicked (dry-run).")
    else:
        print(f"sable-reconcile-handoffs: {len(stranded)} stranded branch(es), "
              f"{filed} for-chuck bead(s) filed{corpus_note}; {held_summary}; "
              f"{kick_candidates} preview-kick candidate(s), {kicked} kicked.")
    return 0


def main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog="sable-reconcile-handoffs")
    parser.add_argument("--repo", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_RC_REPO", os.getcwd()))
    parser.add_argument("--remote", default=os.environ.get("SABLE_RC_REMOTE", "origin"))
    parser.add_argument("--age-min", type=float,
                        default=float(os.environ.get("SABLE_RECONCILE_AGE_MIN", "10")),
                        help="push-age threshold in minutes before a branch is "
                             "eligible for reconciliation (default 10; "
                             "SABLE_RECONCILE_AGE_MIN)")
    parser.add_argument("--hold-stale-days", type=float,
                        default=float(os.environ.get(
                            "SABLE_HOLD_STALE_DAYS", str(DEFAULT_HOLD_STALE_DAYS))),
                        help="a hold older than this many days is flagged "
                             "NEEDING REVIEW in the summary so it cannot decay "
                             "into a permanent quiet veto (default 3; "
                             "SABLE_HOLD_STALE_DAYS)")
    parser.add_argument("--dry-run", action="store_true",
                        help="classify + print only; file no beads; exit 0")
    args = parser.parse_args(argv)
    return reconcile(args.repo, args.remote, args.age_min, args.dry_run,
                     args.hold_stale_days)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    sys.exit(main())
